# 2️⃣ PUT API error (main issue)

Nee error:

```
ObjectOptimisticLockingFailureException
Row was already updated or deleted
```

This happens because **update logic wrong ga undi**.

Probably nuvvu service lo direct ga ila chesav:

```java
public Student updateById(Student s){
    return repo.save(s);
}
```

But Hibernate ki clarity undadu **record exist avuthunda leda**.

---

## Correct Update Logic

Update mundu **record exist avuthunda check cheyyali**.

### Service

```java
public Student updateById(Integer id, Student s){

    Student existing = repo.findById(id).orElse(null);

    if(existing != null){
        existing.setName(s.getName());
        existing.setCourse(s.getCourse());
        return repo.save(existing);
    }

    return null;
}
```

---

### Controller

```java
@PutMapping("/{id}")
public Student updateById(@PathVariable Integer id,
                          @RequestBody Student s){
    return ss.updateById(id,s);
}
```

---

### Postman PUT request

```
PUT
http://localhost:8080/student/1
```

Body:

```json
{
"name":"Hemanth Kumar",
"course":"Spring Boot Advanced"
}
```

Then response:

```json
{
"id":1,
"name":"Hemanth Kumar",
"course":"Spring Boot Advanced"
}
```

